      * T62-DOUBLE-DOWN-ANYTIME -- VERIFY DD RULE VIOLATION (FR44)
      * STORY 6.2: DOUBLE DOWN AFTER HIT MUST BE ACCEPTED (BUG PRESENT)
      * LOOP-A HAS NO IF WS-PC = 2 GUARD BEFORE ACCEPTING D INPUT
       IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
       PROGRAM-ID. T62-DOUBLE-DOWN-ANYTIME.
       ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
       DATA DIVISION.
       WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
           COPY WS-HANDS.
           COPY WS-GAME.
       PROCEDURE DIVISION.
       MAIN-1.
           DISPLAY "=== T62: DOUBLE-DOWN-ANYTIME RULE VIOLATION ==="
           MOVE ZEROS TO WS-HND
           MOVE ZEROS TO WS-GM
           *> SETUP: PLAYER HAS ALREADY HIT -- 3 CARDS IN HAND
           MOVE 3   TO WS-PC
           MOVE 20  TO WS-BET
           MOVE 'D' TO WS-FLG-A
           DISPLAY "  WS-PC=" WS-PC
           DISPLAY "  (WS-PC=3 MEANS POST-HIT -- SHOULD BLOCK DD)"
           DISPLAY "  WS-BET BEFORE: " WS-BET
           *> REPLICATE LOOP-A D BRANCH -- NO WS-PC = 2 GUARD EXISTS
           *> CORRECT CODE WOULD CHECK: IF WS-PC NOT = 2 GO TO LOOP-A
           IF WS-FLG-A = 'D'
               COMPUTE WS-BET = WS-BET * 2
               DISPLAY "  WS-BET AFTER DD: " WS-BET
               DISPLAY "  BUG: DD ACCEPTED WITH WS-PC=3 (EXPECT 40)"
           END-IF
           IF WS-BET NOT = 0040
               DISPLAY "  FAIL: EXPECTED WS-BET=0040 GOT " WS-BET
               MOVE 1 TO RETURN-CODE
               STOP RUN
           END-IF
           DISPLAY "  MISSING GUARD: IF WS-PC = 2 -- NOT IN LOOP-A"
           DISPLAY "=== T62 COMPLETE ==="
           STOP RUN.
